node.text:
“SOME DEMONS AREN’T WORTH FIGHTING”
-
8/8, THIS SUNDAY (TOMORROW)
5PM EST 2PM PST
-
This shirt blank is a god damn crowning achievement for us. It’s an 11.5 oz cotton jersey that feels like those heavy-weight Snoop Dogg Vetements t-shirts. I’m telling you right now, may I get struck by lightning if I’m exaggerating, this is one best quality shirts I’ve ever touched with my callused, stubby fingers. This is what we’ll be using for our dyed blanks from now on. Black shirts and hoodies will remain the same.
-
This will be a part of the WESTERN PULP series. Each piece will come with its own “private” trading card that reveals the short backstory of the character or scene. I will not be post these cards online and I encourage purchasers not to post them either.

“DESERT CANVAS” 
-
DROPPING TODAY
7/18
5PM EST 2PM PST
-
This Reaper uses a heavy, distressed canvas for the upper. It is a light tan/natural color. I’m not the first guy to do this, but these are also pretty simple to dye yourself, like I did in the next slide using the colors from the “LAY DOWN YOUR PISTOL” shirt. Use whatever you have…I used leather dye and paint mixed with water
-

node.text:
Hand-painted Hermès Birkin 35 with fully chain-stitched bandana, hand-done by the master himself @tuljutargate 
-
“A HOT DAY IN THE DESERT”
-
This is the first time I’ve used a brush in forever..with a mix of pen and some pastel overlay. Couldn’t be happier with the final product. My man Tul, absolutely murdered the bandana. Thank you again brother.
